.Dt RXTERM 1
.Os KTH_KRB
.Sh NAME
.Nm rxterm
.Nd
start a secure remote xterm
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm rxterm
.Ar host
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
program starts a
.Nm xterm
window on host
.Ar host .
From this window you will also be able to run X clients that will be
able to connect securily to your X server.
.Sh EXAMPLE
To login from host
.Va foo
(where your display is)
to host
.Va bar ,
you might do the following.
.Bl -enum
.It
On foo: 
.Nm
.Va bar
.It
You will get a new window running an
.Nm xterm
on host
.Va bar .
In this window you will be able to start X clients.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr rxtelnet 1 ,
